description.narrative: (Kenya): The Kenya Medical Supplies Authority (KEMSA) is a commercial parastatal whose functions include procurement, warehousing, and distribution of medications and medical supplies. The KEMSA Medical Commodities Project will procure and distribute maternal and newborn health equipment, and ancillary equipment for contraceptive implants, in collaboration with the Ministry of Health's Division of Reproductive Health, Maternal, and Child Health. The project will warehouse and distribute USAID-procured contraceptives from the central warehouse to over 7,000 public sector health facilities in all of Kenya's 47 counties. In addition, the project will support warehousing and distribution for the U.S. President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR) commodities and the U.S. President's Malaria Initiative (PMI)-procured rapid diagnostics tests and malaria medicines from the central warehouse to public sector health facilities nationwide. Utilizing a Kenyan corporation for the procurement, warehousing, and distribution of medications and medical supplies is a key element to ensure sustainability upon project completion, which is vital to achieving the Kenya Integrated Country Strategy Goal 3, and U.S. Department of State and USAID Joint Strategic Plan 2018-2022 objective 2.2 "Promote healthy, educated, and productive populations in partner countries to drive inclusive and sustainable development, open new markets, and support U.S. prosperity and security objectives." Improving global public health supports the Administration's priority of asserting U.S. leadership and influence..
